      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="lead-big" style="font-size: 19px;">Great things to come.....</span></p>
<p>We are in the process of redeveloping all of our undergraduate degree programmes and plan to offer several new specialist routes, including analytics and human resource management. The Business School made a submission to REF for the first time in 2021 and we are now reflecting on how to build on that work to develop a reputation for business research that aligns with the university-wide commitment to social justice.</p>
<p>The Business School at Queen Margaret University has a real focus on the student experience and developing opportunities for applied and authentic learning.</p>
<p>Small year groups mean we get to know our students and can work collaboratively with them to develop and enhance our programmes. </p>
<p>We have a number of vacancies to help us get to where we want to be and we want you to come along on our journey!</p>
<p><span class="lead-big">Our Vacancies</span></p>
<p><span class="test">We would love to hear from you if you have experience and an interest in <strong>Business Analytics, Digital Marketing and e-Business, Organisational Strategy, and Logistics and Supply Chain Management</strong></span></p>
<p>Click on the tabs for more information on our vacancies for:</p>
<ul>
<li><span class="test">Associate Head of Business, Enterprise and Management (1FTE)</span></li>
<li><span class="test">Reader in Management (1FTE)</span></li>
<li><span class="test">Lecturer in Management (1FTE)</span></li>
<li><span class="test">Lecturer in Management (Business Law - 0.5 FTE)</span></li>
</ul>]]></Value>
    </bodyTop>
    <centralBlocks>
      <Value><![CDATA[[
  {
    "key": "971e67dc-bab2-4020-81bc-4afe1d9355d2",
    "name": "About QMU",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "About QMU",
    "content": "<p><img src=\"?mode=crop&amp;width=800\" alt=\"A panoramic view of QMU campus\" width=\"800\" height=\"266.6666666666667\" data-udi=\"umb://media/d9348bd929454fbca712d38d5401f705\"></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">About QMU</span></p>\n<p>We aim to shape a better world through education, research and innovation. In doing so, we enable individuals and communities to flourish. <br><br>Our person-centred approach to learning makes us stand out from other universities, along with our focus on making society better. Our academic offering also distinguishes us. We dedicate ourselves to subjects where we can provide a distinctive offering - in healthcare; social sciences; creative arts; business; management and enterprise; and primary and secondary teaching.<br><br>Outward looking, we have a strong ethos of partnership and collaboration. At our modern campus, we benefit from easy access to the centre of Edinburgh, Scotland's vibrant and historic capital city.</p>\n<p>We are pioneers in inclusiveness and we embrace people from all backgrounds.<br><br>Find out more about the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/a67713586dab42108759e724aece703d}\" title=\"History\">history of university</a>, along with information about <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/c193260b558648f29c85d69c8c088b80}\" title=\"Quality\">our governance</a>, the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/1bf80f3b042746249bae3810ecc8ca7d}\" title=\"Chancellor, Vice-Chancellor and Senior Leadership Team\">Principal and Vice-Chancellor,</a> <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/1bf80f3b042746249bae3810ecc8ca7d}\" title=\"Chancellor, Vice-Chancellor and Senior Leadership Team\">the senior leadership team</a> and <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/23ed7ab2bf2b4808b948dca16bea8636}\" title=\"Partnerships\">our collaborative partners</a>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">About the QMU Business School</span></p>\n<p>Located within the <a href=\"/schools-and-divisions/\" title=\"School of Arts, Social Sciences and Management\">School of Arts, Social Sciences and Management</a>, <a href=\"/schools-and-divisions/business-school/\" title=\"Queen Margaret Business School\">Queen Margaret Business School</a> delivers a range of undergraduate programs including: Business Management, Business Management with Finance, <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/930798c9c17c4a49892aca843757bc4a}\" title=\"Vacancies\">Business Management with Digital Marketing</a>, Business Management with Analytics, and International Hospitality, Tourism and Events.  Postgraduate programs within the division include International Management and Leadership, Accounting and Finance, International Marketing and Gastronomy. The Business School has a developing research profile and was submitted to REF for the first time in 2021.</p>\n<p>These roles would be to join this exciting division and become a full and active member of the vibrant and <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/930798c9c17c4a49892aca843757bc4a}\" title=\"Vacancies\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">committed team</span></a>.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "0dfa5edd-79ab-4a42-bfad-fa271d5d9c53",
    "name": "Full time roles",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Full time roles",
    "content": "<p><img src=\"?width=789&amp;height=262&amp;mode=max\" alt=\"QMU students in business seminar\" width=\"789\" height=\"262\" data-udi=\"umb://media/b2e5cbdb6ef241918482f10a23ddf8ce\"></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">Join us for an exciting journey</span></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: circle;\">\n<li><strong>3</strong> x <strong>Full Time Positions</strong> – \n<ul style=\"list-style-type: circle;\">\n<li>Associate Head of Division</li>\n<li>Reader in Management</li>\n<li>Lecturer in Management</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"lead\"><strong>School: </strong></span>Arts, Social Sciences and Management<br><span class=\"lead\"><strong>Division: </strong></span><a href=\"/schools-and-divisions/business-school/\" title=\"Business, Enterprise and Management\">Business, Enterprise and Management</a><br><span class=\"lead\"><strong>Responsible to: </strong></span>Head of Division<br><span class=\"lead\"><strong>Location: </strong></span>Edinburgh (<a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/a713799de0204325bb063efbd482f213}\" title=\"Location and Getting Here\">Musselburgh Campus</a>)/ Hybrid Working</p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\"></span><span class=\"lead\"></span><strong>Closing Date for all: 9th October 2022</strong></p>\n<p>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Associate Head of Division </span></p>\n<p><strong>Contract Basis:</strong> Permanent, open ended (3 year tenure then revert to substantive role of Reader or Senior Lecturer or renewed for further 3 year tenure)<br><strong>Contract Type:</strong> Teaching and Research<br><strong>Hours:</strong> Full Time, 35 hours per week (1FTE)<br><strong>Salary/Grade:</strong> Grade 9 - £53,353 to £61,823 (with possible progression to £73,786)</p>\n<p><strong>REF: CRBE001C</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/5c52b9b0b50c46b2a431feb29fc7c5e1}\" title=\"Associate Head of Business, Enterprise and Management Job Description\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Associate Head of Division - Job Description and Person Specification</span></a></p>\n<p>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br></p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Reader in Management</span></p>\n<p><strong>Contract Basis:</strong> Permanent, open ended<br><strong>Contract Type:</strong> Teaching and Research<br><strong>Hours:</strong> Full Time, 35 hours per week (1 FTE)<br><strong>Salary/Grade:</strong> Grade 9 - £53,353 to £61,823 (with possible progression to £73,786)</p>\n<p><strong>REF:</strong> <strong>CVRM081A</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/8e8aec3bf33249c1a5f58282b7053760}\" title=\"Reader in Management Job Description and Person Specification\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Reader in Management - Job Description and Person Specification</span></a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Lecturer in Management</span></p>\n<p><strong>Contract Basis:</strong> Permanent, open ended<br><strong>Contract Type:</strong> Teaching and Research<br><strong>Hours:</strong> Full Time<br><strong>Salary/Grade: </strong>Grade 8 - £40,931 to £51,805 (with possible progression to £58,284)</p>\n<p><strong>REF:</strong> <strong>CRMV080A</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/6d2595f3331647c198fb3171f5d15e74}\" title=\"Lecturer in Management Job Description and Person Specification\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Lecturer in Management - Job Description and Person Specification</span></a></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "9cdb3db3-3487-459f-8186-b6835a6bb6a4",
    "name": "Part time roles",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Part time roles",
    "content": "<p><img src=\"?width=790&amp;height=264&amp;mode=max\" alt=\"QMU students in seminar\" width=\"790\" height=\"264\" data-udi=\"umb://media/333dc46fb73940768139196c0590b816\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph;\" class=\"Default\"><span class=\"lead lead-big\" style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Queen Margaret University Business School is looking for an excellent, legally educated lecturer to join their team.</span></p>\n<p>It is an exciting time to join the Business School. We are in the process of redeveloping all our undergraduate degree programmes and plan to offer several new specialist routes, with various aspects of business law throughout each.</p>\n<p>We have a real focus on the student experience and developing opportunities for applied and authentic learning. Small year groups mean we get to know our students and can work collaboratively with them to enhance the learning experience. We also focus on developing transferable skills and positive graduate attributes, which for example is why we are looking for someone who can help teach our students how to negotiate.</p>\n<p>The successful candidate will be able to deliver excellent teaching and pursue innovative scholarship in the field of business law and dispute resolution. You may have some previous experience as a university lecturer but most importantly you will be a committed educator, supervisor, and outstanding communicator. The role will require you to contribute to a range of teaching, scholarship, pastoral, and administrative activities across the division. You will be passionate about the student experience and will be committed to a teaching approach that integrates theory and practice.</p>\n<p>With the legal and other knowledge required to teach across a range of undergraduate and postgraduate modules, you will also have specialist expertise related to employment law, mediation, or negotiation.</p>\n<p>You will have or be willing to work towards a relevant teaching qualification and exhibit a clear ability to work collegiately with others to deliver set objectives. You will either have a PhD in a relevant subject area (applicants should either already hold a PhD or be close to completion), or another relevant postgraduate qualification along with significant professional experience.</p>\n<p>Ideally, you will already have a track record of working with industry partners and be prepared to forge new links across the city, region and beyond to develop opportunities in student education, placements, academic scholarship, consultancy and/or impact.  We have a track record delivering commercially successful training in dispute resolution and law, so we need someone with a ‘can do’ spirit and a sense of customer focus. You may also be required to liaise and support colleagues at our transnational partners who deliver our business degrees. </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead lead-big\">Lecturer in Management (Business Law)</span></p>\n<p><strong>School: </strong>Arts, Social Sciences and Management<br><strong>Division:</strong> <a href=\"/schools-and-divisions/business-school/\" title=\"Business, Enterprise and Management\">Business, Enterprise and Management</a><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/6e5272fa3f544060af877ca7f121f21c}\" title=\"Psychology, Sociology and Education\"></a><br><strong>Responsible to: </strong>Head of Division<br><strong>Location: </strong>Edinburgh (<a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/a713799de0204325bb063efbd482f213}\" title=\"Location and Getting Here\">Musselburgh Campus</a>) / Hybrid Working</p>\n<p>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p><strong>Contract Basis:</strong> Permanent, open ended<br><strong>Contract Type:</strong> Teaching and Scholarship<br><strong>Hours:</strong> Part Time, 17.5 hours per week (0.5 FTE)<br><strong>Salary/Grade:</strong> Grade 8 £40,931 - £51,805 (with possible progression to £58,284) per annum pro rata<br><br><strong>Closing Date:</strong> Sunday 9th October 2022</p>\n<p><strong>REF:</strong> <strong>CRTM014A</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/77f12f1951a4466ca8ed33c0ab6c6f2e}\" title=\"Lecturer in Management (Business Law) Job Description and Person Specification\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Lecturer in Management (Business Law) - Job Description and Person Specification</span></a></p>\n<p>This role does not meet the minimum requirements set by UKVI to enable sponsorship of migrant workers. Therefore, we cannot progress applications from candidates who require sponsorship to work in the UK.</p>\n<p> </p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "553a3c72-6cdb-409a-9caf-13e7bd55094c",
    "name": "What we offer",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "What we offer",
    "content": "<p><img src=\"?width=793&amp;height=265&amp;mode=max\" alt=\"QMU logo in blue against a white background\" width=\"793\" height=\"265\" data-udi=\"umb://media/1dfa730a810a41c5a80408cf1a8ae78c\"></p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">What we Offer</span></p>\n<p>We are committed to equality of opportunity for all by providing a supportive and flexible and inclusive working environment, and we welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds. We are proud to hold an Athena SWAN Bronze Award which recognises the advancement of gender equality at QMU.</p>\n<p>We support a flexible approach to work as well additional benefits to help your work life balance such as a generous annual leave allowance, subsidised on-site gym membership, bike to work scheme and a range of discounts.</p>\n<p>We invest in your professional development, including through access to AdvanceHE Strategic Leadership programmes and HE sector mentoring through access to TRAMS.</p>\n<p>We are very proud of our <a href=\"/media/5lhbvhwh/qmu-equality-calendar-2022.pdf\" title=\"Inclusion Calendar\">Inclusion Calendar</a></p>\n<p>We also offer:</p>\n<p>1. Wellbeing support with our 24 hour Employee Assistance Service, access to mental health support services and occupational health support</p>\n<p>2. Discounted <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/854bacf0350b4399af7c7ec40cbea646}\" title=\"QMU Sports Centre\">sports and leisure facilities</a> on campus</p>\n<p>3. Access to our <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/71b99825061d4a2e8bd48daeb9d7cfe2}\" title=\"Library\">learning resource centre</a></p>\n<p>4. Interest free travel loans</p>\n<p>5. Access to a variety of learning and development opportunities</p>\n<p>6. Subscription to meditation app</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "2490685e-c051-4560-8b57-7f1648d03aba",
    "name": "How to apply",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "How to apply",
    "content": "<p><span class=\"lead-big\">How to Apply<br /><br /></span>Please visit the QMU Vacancies page using the links below to view the job description for all posts and to download the application form. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://ce0011li.webitrent.com/ce0011li_webrecruitment/wrd/run/ETREC105GF.open?WVID=6368270VSq\" title=\"Apply Now\" data-anchor=\"?WVID=6368270VSq\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Apply Now</span></a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>While applicants will be able to include a CV with their applications, the application form should be completed in full, and answers should explicitly make clear how you meet all the criteria marked on the job description.</strong></p>\n<p>For informal queries please contact Dr. Majella Sweeney, Head of Business School via email <a href=\"mailto:MSweeney@qmu.ac.uk\">MSweeney@qmu.ac.uk</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Should you have any queries regarding the application process or require any special assistance please contact Human Resources on email <a href=\"mailto:recruitment@qmu.ac.uk\" title=\"Email QMU Recruitment Team\"><span>recruitment@qmu.ac.uk</span></a>.</p>\n<p>Applicants should be available to start in role ideally at the beginning of January 2023.</p>\n<p><strong>Closing Date for all Applications is Sunday 9<sup>th</sup> October 2022.</strong></p>\n<p>As a university, we are committed to the <a href=\"https://www.vitae.ac.uk/policy/concordat\" title=\"Researcher Development Concordat\">Researcher Development Concordat</a> and were, in fact, the first Scottish Higher Education Institute (and part of the first UK cohort of institutes) to publicly declare our commitment to its principles.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Queen Margaret University is committed to equality of opportunity for all by providing a supportive, flexible and inclusive working environment, and we welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds. Please have a look at our <a href=\"/media/5lhbvhwh/qmu-equality-calendar-2022.pdf\" title=\"Inclusion Calendar\">Diversity, Wellbeing and Inclusion Calendar.</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We are proud to hold an Athena SWAN Bronze Award which recognises the advancement of gender equality at QMU. Find out more about <a href=\"https://www.ecu.ac.uk/equality-charters/athena-swan/\" title=\"Athena Swan\">Athena SWAN </a>.  We have a number of family friendly policies and are happy to consider job share applications.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We are a Disability Confident Employer, should you require any specific arrangements during the recruitment process please note this on your application form or contact Human Resources on 0131 474 0000 or email <a href=\"mailto:recruitment@qmu.ac.uk\" title=\"Email QMU Recruitment Team\">recruitment@qmu.ac.uk</a></p>"
  }
]]]></Value>
